@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Chain_Gang" where
you want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other
files or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 8 colours.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Chain_Gang runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a tile containing a chainlink (or any movable
tile) you want to move, and while holding the mouse button move the
mouse pointer to an empty tile where you want to move the tile and
release the mouse button (in a drag and drop manner), if the move
is possible, the tile will go there.

  Chainlinks must be connected with other chainlinks of the same
colour. Also, the links can only be connected with a compatible
type of link: an horizontal link can be connected with an other
horizontal (or 4-way) link if it is beside it, the same thing goes
for a vertical link that can be connected with an other vertical
(or 4-way) link, as long as it is located above the other.

  When you complete a chain with at least 3 chainlinks, it is
removed from the game board. A chain with 3 chainlinks will give
you 1 point, but if you create a chain using 4 chainlinks or more,
you get more points, as is shown below:

      4 chainlinks   =  10 points
      5 chainlinks   =  20 points
      6 chainlinks   =  40 points
      7 chainlinks   =  80 points
      8 chainlinks   = 160 points
      9 chainlinks   = 320 points

  Every time you move a chainlink and it doesn't complete a chain
of at least 3 chainlinks, three more chainlinks are added on the
game board... don't let the game board fill up completely, because
when that happens, the game is over. When chainlinks are added to
the game board, they may complete chains, these chains will be
removed from the board, but you will get no points.

  As you progress in the game, 'special' tiles will appear from
time to time, these tiles are:

-Non-movable chainlinks: these are indicated by a tile that is
                         'pressed down' and they are just that:
non-movable, but you can link them to other compatible chainlinks.

-Movable blocks: These can be moved to any empty space you choose.
                 Movable blocks cannot be eliminated.

-Unmovable blocks: These blocks, indicated by a brick wall pattern,
                   obviously cannot be moved. As it is with the
movable blocks, they serve no other purpose than being in the way
when they are not needed. These types of blocks cannot be removed
and will remain where they are until the end of the game.

-Bombs: These are indicated by an 'electric flash'-like icon. They
        can be clicked on where they are or be moved on any empty
tile. When you release the mouse button on a bomb tile, 'lightning'
bolts start from the tile in 4 directions and eliminate all the
chainlinks that are on their path, those lightning bolts are only
stopped by movable or unmovable blocks or the game board's edges.
Each chainlink that is eliminated by a lightning bolt will give 10
points. Note that if a lightning bolt eliminate part of a chain,
the connecting link with the removed chainlink will remain, but the
lone chainlink cannot be moved afterwards. However, it can be
reconnected with any compatible chainlink.

  Have fun!

  A 'Minimize game window' button, indicated by a small triangle
icon, which is located on the lower left of the window, minimize
the size of the game window while keeping the same gameboard tile
size.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

